    {
      "id": "26.9_notes",
      "type": "body",
      "section": "26.9",
      "text": "Notes:\n1. Conservative approximation Ke = 1.00 is permitted in all cases.\n2. Factor Ke shall be determined from Table 26.9-1 using interpolation or from the following formula for all elevations: Ke = e^(-0.0000362ze) (ze = ground elevation above sea level, ft); or Ke = e^(-0.00011877ze) (ze = ground elevation above sea level, m).\n3. Ke is permitted to be taken as 1.00 in all cases.",
